attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit MSB executable, ARM, version 1 (ARM), statically linked, no section header

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This sample is a highly sophisticated ARM-based IoT botnet agent, likely belonging to the Gafgyt or Mirai families. It utilizes the MQTT protocol (revealed by the 'MQTT' string construction in sub_e168) for Command and Control (C2) communications over SSL/TLS. The binary features extensive use of OpenSSL for AES-256-CBC encrypted configuration (sub_b3f4) and recursive file system manipulation/deletion capabilities (sub_a9fc). Key malicious behaviors include system information exfiltration via HTTP/JSON POST requests, dynamic command execution using dlsym-resolved symbols (sub_a3c8), and self-deletion routines (sub_d4a8). IOCs include the use of UPX packing, MQTT protocol constants, and hardcoded C2 communication templates for application/json content types.
